Sinohydro in Talks for $1.2 Bln Costa Rica Project, Daily Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-10T00:09:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/sinohydro-in-talks-for-1-2-bln-costa-rica-project-daily-says.html
Sinohydro Corp.,  China ’s largest
hydropower construction company, is in talks with the Costa
Rican government for a $1.2 billion contract to build a 300-
megawatt hydroelectric power station in the country, the  China
Daily  reported, citing the South American country’s ambassador.  The Chinese state-owned dam builder is expected to win the
project from the Costa Rican Institute of Electricity, the
report said.  The plant is scheduled to go into operation in 2016 as a
joint venture between Sinohydro and the institute, Marco Vinicio
Ruiz Gutierrez, the Costa Rican ambassdor to China, was cited as
saying by the newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 swong139@bloomberg.net  